HISTCLEAN(1) ["" ["General Commands Manual"]]

# NAME

histclean - clean shell history file

# SYNOPSIS

*histclean* [options]

# DESCRIPTION

Clean duplicate shell commands from history files in-place, while
preserving the most recent unique occurrence of each command.

# OPTIONS

*-h*, *--help*
	Show help message and exit.

*-d*, *--dry-run*
	Print deduplicated history to stdout without modifying the file.

*-b*, *--backup*
	Create a .backup copy before modifying.

*-i*, *--input* <file>
	Read from <file> instead of the default.

*-o*, *--output* <file>
	Write to <file> instead of overwriting the input.
